events.description: Russia founds a colony on Kodiak Island, Alaska.

events.html: • 1790 – Northwest Indian War: Native American forces defeat the United States, ending the Harmar Campaign.[6]

events.description: Sam Houston is inaugurated as the first President of the Republic of Texas.

events.description: A plebiscite ratifies the annexation of Veneto and Mantua to Italy, which had occurred three days before on October 19.

events.description: The first telegraphic connection in Argentina becomes operational.
events.html: • 1875 – The first telegraphic connection in Argentina becomes operational.

events.description: The Blantyre mining disaster in Scotland kills 207 miners.
events.html: • 1877 – The Blantyre mining disaster in Scotland kills 207 miners.

events.description: The Bramall Lane stadium sees the first rugby match played under floodlights.
events.html: • 1878 – The Bramall Lane stadium sees the first rugby match played under floodlights.

events.description: The royalist Leonardopoulos–Gargalidis coup d'état attempt fails in Greece, discrediting the monarchy and paving the way for the establishment of the Second Hellenic Republic.

events.html: • 1934 – In East Liverpool, Ohio, FBI agents shoot and kill notorious bank robber Pretty Boy Floyd.
